## 8. Complexity summary

| Operation | Time | Notes |
|-----------|------|-------|
| `heappush` | O(log n) | sift-up |
| `heappop` | O(log n) | sift-down |
| `heapify` | **O(n)** | not O(n log n) |
| peek (`h[0]`) | O(1) | read root only |
| `nlargest(k, iter)` | O(n log k) | |
| `nsmallest(k, iter)` | O(n log k) | |

**Space**: O(n) for the heap array.

**Height**: ⌊log₂ n⌋ — a heap of 1,000,000 elements has a height of ~20.

