One thing to watch immediately given your patterns: the `list.sort()` returns `None` bug you've hit before has a natural cousin here. `heapq.heappop(h)` **returns** the value — never discard it. And `heapq.heappush(h, x)` returns `None` — the heap is modified in-place. These are the two operations you'll call hundreds of times; make sure the return-vs-side-effect distinction is automatic.

